! $Id: findu,v 1.2 2001/12/08 17:00:48 toast Exp $
Usage: FINDU [-switch [<arg>]] <userhost_mask> [<server>]
  Searches for a user matching the supplied user@host mask on a
  server.  The following switches are also recognized and used to
  limit the listing:
  -CLASS <num>            - Shows only users in the connection
			    class given.
  -COUNT                  - Does not show matches. Only counts
			    them.

  The switches may be abbreviated unambiguously.

See Also:
  FINDD
  FINDK
  TRACE
